The correlation network's extraction

Source: R/pNetCor.R
pNetCor.Rd

The correlation network's extraction

Usage

pNetCor(
  dat_meta,
  dat_gene,
  cor_method = "pearson",
  cor_threshold = 0.9,
  p_threshold = 0.01
)

Arguments

dat_meta

the metabolite data, the row is the metabolite's KEGGID, and the column is the sample

dat_gene

the gene expression data, the row is the gene symbol, and the column is the sample

cor_method

specifies the type of correlations to compute. Spearman correlations are the Pearson linear correlations computed on the ranks of non-missing elements, using midranks for ties.

cor_threshold

the cutoff of correlation coefficient

p_threshold

the cutoff of correlation p value

Value

a figure and a data frame

Examples

res <- pNetCor(meta_dat, gene_dat)
#> [1] "Starting correlation calculation"
